Business Brief -- Nichiboshin Ltd.:
   Six Banks Said Lowering
   Rates on Company's Loans
The group of banks also will provide about two billion yen
in an emergency loan to the company and dispatch executive
personnel to work on the company's financial rehabilitation,
the sources said. They said the group includes Dai-Ichi
Kangyo Bank and Yasuda Trust  Banking Co.
   Nichiboshin, established in 1957, ran into financial
trouble as a result of excessive lending for real estate
transactions over the past five years.
   The company's balance of loans outstanding totaled 1.238
trillion yen at the end of 1991, about 40% of which was
loaned by the six main banks, Kyodo reported.